text: Cardedu (Cardèdu) is a town and comune (municipality) in the Province of Nuoro in Sardinia, Italy. As of 2016, 1,909 people lived there. It has an area of 33.39 km². It is located at 19 meters above sea level. == References == == Other websites == Category:Communes of the Province of Nuoro
title: Cardedu
